1. run the server script
  $ chmod +x server.sh
  $ ./server.sh

Note: name the NIS server example.com (or whatever is the default)

2. press Ctrl-D when asked to add another NIS server besides server.example.com,
   then press 'y' to confirm the list of NIS servers.
   
reference website (server): https://www.server-world.info/en/note?os=Debian_8&p=nis&f=1
reference website (clients): https://www.server-world.info/en/note?os=Debian_8&p=nis&f=2
